  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Accounts Executive",
  "description": "<p><strong>Company Overview / Employee Value Proposition</strong></p><p>E3 Design Pte Ltd specializes in commercial outfitting. E3 offers valued clients a comprehensive suite of services from design consultancy, project management, design, and build to interior fit-out.</p><p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>You will manage financial accounting processes and collaborate with stakeholders to deliver accurate financial reporting, supporting strategic financial planning and compliance within the Construction/Interior Design industry.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Prepare complete sets of accounts to ensure accurate financial records and compliance with industry standards</li><li>Assist in compiling financial reports and statements to support management decision-making</li><li>Participate in financial planning, budgeting, and forecasting processes to drive effective resource allocation</li><li>Collaborate with internal and external auditors to ensure compliance with financial regulations and reporting accuracy</li><li>Develop and maintain professional relationships with internal teams and external stakeholders to facilitate smooth financial operations</li><li>Deliver timely financial reporting and updates to management for informed business decisions</li><li>Execute additional duties or projects assigned by management to support business objectives</li></ul><p><strong>Required competencies and certifications</strong></p><ul><li>Demonstrated experience in accounts payable (AP) and accounts receivable (AR) with at least 2 years in the Construction/Interior Design industry</li><li>Proficiency in Microsoft Office applications to efficiently manage financial data and reporting</li><li>Ability to work independently and maintain a task-oriented approach in a fast-paced environment</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Immediate availability to join the team is preferred</li></ul><p><strong>Other Information</strong></p><ul><li>Work schedule: 5 days per week</li><li>Convenient location near MRT</li><li>Employee benefits include annual leave, medical leave, wellness claims, and company events</li><li>Opportunities for career progression, training, and development</li></ul>",
